Ask HN: Why is testosterone a scheduled substance in the USA?
text:
It seems like in 1990 the USA banned testosterone across the nation, but estrogen can easily be picked up over the counter?

Why the double standards here? If I’m a non competing athlete that wants balanced hormones and a healthy sex drive I should be able to do this right?

Not to mention many people who identify as trans find it difficult to get testosterone too.

What do we need to do to appeal this?

Show HN: A Distributed, Serverless Cloud Powered by Browser Tabs
text:
I made a crowd-computing FaaS platform that runs your functions in a Web Worker based on provided policy. I figured this would be useful for leveraging a computer lab full of computers without having to install software on each one among other things.

Still not perfect but any feedback would be welcome and if you want to use it, by all means! Also if anyone has demo/application ideas, I'd really appreciate that.

Open Source: https://github.com/dvtate/xssfaas

Guides: https://github.com/dvtate/xssfaas/wiki
